        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/24445",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Internally, the constraint uses strstr. We could potentially utilize the mb_stristr() variant, but has mbstring is not installed on vanilla PHP installs, this would require adding an additional test to determine if the the extension is present.\n\nDeferring for a while.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-09-11T07:10:08.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-09-11T07:10:08.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/24543",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=zimnyx",
                        "name": "zimnyx",
                        "displayName": "Piotr Czachur",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Matthew,\n\nAre you sure it's strstr() issue?\nI've just lunched XDebug and take a look on strstr() arguments inside Zend_Test_PHPUnit_Constraint_DomQuery::_matchContent().\nWhat I have noticed is that $this->_getNodeContent($node); returns string 'Autoryzacja nie powiod\u00c5<82>a si\u00c4<99>'. This spoiled string is passed to strstr(). ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=zimnyx",
                        "name": "zimnyx",
                        "displayName": "Piotr Czachur",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-09-15T02:32:11.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-09-15T02:32:11.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/26888",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=zimnyx",
                        "name": "zimnyx",
                        "displayName": "Piotr Czachur",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Matthew,\n\nTo  replicate this bug create simple view with non-ascii unicode string:\n============\n<p>\u0142\u0105ka<\/p>\n============\n\nThen in controller test add:\n============\n$this->assertQueryContentContains('p', '\u0142\u0105ka'); \n============\n\nIt should pass, but doesn't.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=zimnyx",
                        "name": "zimnyx",
                        "displayName": "Piotr Czachur",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-12-02T00:35:12.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-12-02T00:35:12.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/28251",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I've done a fair bit of research, and this appears to be a problem with libxml. When I call $doc->saveXML(), I receive the document with all UTF-8 characters represented as HTML entities; however, when I call $doc->saveXML($node), I get a different string entirely -- no HTML entities, and different characters than the original.\n\nYou can verify this by adding the following two lines following line 193 of Zend\/Dom\/Query.php:\n\n{code}\necho $domDoc->saveXML() . \"\\n\\n\";\nforeach ($nodeList as $node) {\n    echo $domDoc->saveXML($node), \"\\n\\n\";\n}\n{code}\n\nI think I need to pass this upstream to the PHP project.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-01-15T16:21:28.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-01-15T16:21:28.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31321",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=zimnyx",
                        "name": "zimnyx",
                        "displayName": "Piotr Czachur",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Matthew, any news?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=zimnyx",
                        "name": "zimnyx",
                        "displayName": "Piotr Czachur",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-05-25T05:27:58.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-25T05:27:58.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31323",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=zimnyx",
                        "name": "zimnyx",
                        "displayName": "Piotr Czachur",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "\nMatthew,\ntake a look, for me saveXML() returns spoiled characters in both situations (PHP 5.2.6):\n\n\n{code}\n$doc = new DOMDocument('1.0', 'UTF-8');\n\n$root = $doc->createElement('book');\n$root = $doc->appendChild($root);\n\n$title = $doc->createElement('title');\n$title = $root->appendChild($title);\n\n$text = $doc->createTextNode('Word with polish character: u\u017cytkownik');\n$text = $title->appendChild($text);\n\necho \"Saving all the document:<br>\\n\";\necho htmlspecialchars($doc->saveXML()) . \"<br>\\n\";\n\necho \"Saving only the title part:<br>\\n\";\necho htmlspecialchars($doc->saveXML($title));\n\n{code}\n\nOutputs\n\n{code}\nSaving all the document:\n<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <book><title>Word with polish character: u\u00c5\u00bcytkownik<\/title><\/book>\nSaving only the title part:\n<title>Word with polish character: u\u00c5\u00bcytkownik<\/title>\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=zimnyx",
                        "name": "zimnyx",
                        "displayName": "Piotr Czachur",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-05-25T06:01:32.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-25T06:01:32.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31324",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=zimnyx",
                        "name": "zimnyx",
                        "displayName": "Piotr Czachur",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "...but in commandline version, with the same php.ini, saveXML() returns valid values:\n{code}\nphp \/var\/www\/test.php \nSaving all the document:<br>&lt;?xml version=&quot;1.0&quot; encoding=&quot;UTF-8&quot;?&gt;\n&lt;book&gt;&lt;title&gt;Word with polish character: u\u017cytkownik&lt;\/title&gt;&lt;\/book&gt;\n<br>Saving only the title part:<br>&lt;title&gt;Word with polish character: u\u017cytkownik&lt;\/title&gt;\n{code}\n\nDefinitely PHP bug, I will report it.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=zimnyx",
                        "name": "zimnyx",
                        "displayName": "Piotr Czachur",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-05-25T06:11:45.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-25T06:11:45.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31325",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=zimnyx",
                        "name": "zimnyx",
                        "displayName": "Piotr Czachur",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Seems to be fixed in 5.2.9, confirmed on Linux and Windows version.\nLet me check if unit test will pass after upgrade to 5.2.9 - I'll be back here soon.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=zimnyx",
                        "name": "zimnyx",
                        "displayName": "Piotr Czachur",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-05-25T06:40:43.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-25T06:40:43.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/47950",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=padraic",
                        "name": "padraic",
                        "displayName": "P\u00e1draic Brady",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Libxml issue has been fixed for a while. ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=padraic",
